3
http://certkill.com
A. There are no initial networking parameters
B. The system has not completed a full POST process
C. The user has insufficient permissions
D. Firmware has just been updated
Answer: D
Explanation: Normally the icons gray out when there are insufficient permissions to
access it. In this case, the icon is not grayed which means that the firmware has just been
updated and there are not more firmware updates to download.

A customer needs a hardware refresh of their G6 servers and is considering the Gen8
platform. What is an advantage of Virtual Media in a Gen8 compared to the G6 platform?
A. USB 3.0
B. USB 2.0
C. Mounting multiple drives simultaneously
D. Mounting zip files
Answer: B
Explanation: HP G6 servers didn’t support USB virtual media. They supported only CD-
ROM. USB 3.0 is still not supported on Gen 8 servers.
